article.headline: Temple 89, La Salle 64
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mark Tyndale scored 22 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as Temple cruised to an 89-64 win over city rival La Salle on Sunday afternoon. Dustin Salisbery finished with 19 points for the Owls, while Atlantic 10 scoring leader Dionte Christmas added 17 while Ryan Brooks came off the bench to score 11. Temple (9-12, 3-5 Atlantic 10) won its second straight game and sealed matters early by shooting 65 percent in the first half, including a remarkable 69 percent (9-for-13) from 3-point range. The Owls broke the game open early with a 20-2 run midway through the first half and led 56-33 at intermission. Kimmani Barrett and Rodney Green each scored 12 points to lead La Salle (9-14, 2-7), which starts three freshman and is in jeopardy of being one of the two A-10 teams that will not qualify for the conference tournament. The Explorers turned the ball over 18 times for the game, including 13 in the first half. La Salle tightened things up and made a brief push midway through the second half, closing to within 73-56 on a Sherman Diaz layup. But Tyndale scored the next six points, punctuating a pair of steals with back-to-back dunks that took the air out of the Explorers' comeback attempt.
